Module kivakit.core.kernel

Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.time

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ModificationTimestamped  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Duration
    A Duration is an immutable length of time stored as a number of milliseconds.
    Duration.Converter
    Converts the given String to a new Duration object.
    Duration.MillisecondsConverter
    Converts milliseconds to and from Duration
    Duration.SecondsConverter
    Converts seconds to and from Duration
    Frequency
    A simple frequency domain object.
    Frequency.Converter
    Converts to and from a frequency, expressed as a duration between cycles.
    LocalTime
    Snapshot of local time at a specific timezone
    Rate
    An abstract rate in Count per Duration.
    RateCalculator
    Calculates a Rate over time as a count is increased by RateCalculator.add(int) or RateCalculator.increment().
    Time
    An immutable Time class that represents a specific point in UNIX time.
    TimeZones
    Utility methods to map between ZoneIds and their display names
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    DayOfWeek
    Enum for days of the week
    Duration.Range
    The range of values allowed for a given duration.
    Meridiem
    Anti-meridiem (AM) or post-meridiem (PM) in the English system of keeping time.
